Now, let's think about how to express this in terms of the product measure structure. The set `{ω | X ω ⊆ u}` can be seen as the set of all `ω` such that for all `i`, if `i ∈ X ω`, then `i ∈ u`. This is equivalent to the intersection over all `i ∉ u` of the set `{ω | i ∉ X ω}`.

